🐜⚡ ANTS ON MY BREADBOARD! ⚡🐜

You know those "marching ants" in circuit simulators that show current flow? 

Yeah, that's real now. On actual hardware.

Latest JumperlOS update adds real-time current visualization to Jumperless V5. The RGB LEDs under each breadboard hole animate to show:
• Current direction (which way electrons are marching)
• Current magnitude (how fast they're marching)
• The actual path through your circuit

Because prototyping in 2025 shouldn't require imagination. Your breadboard should just SHOW you what's happening.

This is why we put 1920 programmable RGB LEDs and current sensors in a breadboard. For wizard shit like this. ✨

