**LinkedIn:**

Excited to share the latest JumperlOS firmware update: real-time current flow visualization for Jumperless V5! 

We've implemented an animated "marching ants" display that leverages the integrated INA219 current sensors and 1920-LED matrix to show:

✅ Current direction and magnitude in real-time
✅ Dynamic speed scaling based on measured current
✅ Full path visualization across the breadboard topology

This feature brings the visual feedback of circuit simulation into physical hardware prototyping - reducing debug time and providing immediate validation of circuit behavior.

The underlying implementation uses sub-millisecond LED refresh rates synchronized with current measurements, creating smooth animations that correlate directly with actual electron flow.

When your development board doubles as a high-resolution display that understands its own circuit topology, you can deliver debugging capabilities that were previously impossible with traditional hardware.

Jumperless V5 continues to push the boundary of what's possible in hardware prototyping - combining software-defined connectivity, integrated measurement tools, and real-time visual feedback into a single development platform.

